https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-wordpress-with-lamp-on-ubuntu-16-04

1) Install Apache:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install apache2
2) Setting up a firewall to allow web traffic:
sudo ufw allow in "Apache Full"
3) Check the installation result by typing in web browser the public IP address of your server:
http://127.0.0.1
4)Install Mysql:
sudo apt install mysql-server
sudo mysql_secure_installation
X4CjFYrrqUxUbUYBvCj364jsKEwUe2xTFsGdDQpgDPQUq6YpgD
5) Setting Mysql:
sudo mysql
SELECT user,authentication_string,plugin,host FROM mysql.user;
6) Change password:
ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'password';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
exit
7)Install php:
sudo apt install php libapache2-mod-php php-mysql
8)Change config file:
sudo nano /etc/apache2/mods-enabled/dir.conf
File :
<IfModule mod_dir.c>
    DirectoryIndex index.html index.cgi index.pl index.php index.xhtml index.htm
</IfModule>
Change to:
<IfModule mod_dir.c>
    DirectoryIndex index.php index.html index.cgi index.pl index.xhtml index.htm
</IfModule>
9)Restart:
sudo systemctl restart apache2
10) Test web php:
sudo nano /var/www/html/info.php
And write:
<?php
phpinfo();
?>
11)Open this adress in browser:
http://127.0.0.1/info.php
